Help on spell: Absent mind.
Casting time: 8 rounds.
Spell cost: 444 SPs.
Spell type: heal.
Spell words: Mhael.
A skilled priest can divide his/her mind and thus be able to control a.
Spell while casting another. This isn't as easy as it sounds though and
many things are known to affect it. Creating this link between the caster
and another target is known to be less effective. The link can be broken by
either the caster or the target at any time. It will automatically wear off
when it can no longer be upkeeped.

Help on spell: Acid arrow.
Casting time: 1 round.
Spell cost: 44 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: acid.
Maximum damage: 145.
Spell words: yluigh bugh.
This spell is very similiar to the more simple spell named Flame arrow.
The only actual difference between the spell of Acid arrow and that of Flame
arrow is the composition of the arrow itself. To become a good spellcaster, an
apprentice must study atleast the basics of alchemy. The hours of studying
pay off upon mastery oft this spell. When succesfully casting this spell, the
caster summons an arrow made of acid. When the arrow materializes the caster
must blast the arrow immediately at his foe or the arrow loses its efficiency
and swiftness. Research indicates that a person with more wisdom is able
to summon a much more powerful arrow. Also, the intelligence of the caster
makes the arrow more efficient. But still, no one has yet found how to summon
an single arrow devastating to take your opponent down, no matter how strong
it would be.

