granting them a great deal of strength, collectively.

Help on spell: Billow of miasma.
Casting time: 4 rounds.
Spell cost: 183 SPs.
Spell type: area attack.
Damage type: asphyxiation.
Maximum damage: 130.
Spell words: Ffulf fo lluf.
With this spell the caster summons a thick cloud of miasma in the room.
The miasma is so thick and suffocating that it makes all the caster's
foes have breathing difficulties, while the experienced caster and his
party of immediate friends are immune to the smoke. In order to make
this spell work, the caster must gather all the filth from the air
and transform it into suffocating miasma. But still after dozens of
hours spent studying this spell the mages have not found how to make
this spell incessant. The suffocating billow of miasma disappears as
fast as it was created, leaving the stronger enemies only slightly
hurt but the weakest might have taken more permanent damage. It is
said that the knowledge of this spell enhances the amount of time
the billow deals damage.

