Maximum damage: 159.
Spell words: judicandus kohtuullista
Affecting stat(s): wis, arcane lore and cure light and serious wounds.

Help on spell: Caustic opposition.
Casting time: 8 rounds.
Spell cost: 375 SPs.
Spell type: defensive.
Spell words: minor subsisto solvo.
This spell is a lesser invulnerability against acid damage.
The caster channels his or her powers to condense moisture
out of the air and enchant the water, turning it into an
adhesive magical liquid that settles on the target's skin.
This liquid neutralizes any caustic substances connecting
with it. Unfortunately, it cannot always fully cover the
protected, thus leaving him or her vulnerable if an attack is
lucky enough to connect with unprotected tissue.

Help on spell: cellular asphyxia
There is no help available for this spell. (UNKNOWN)
No such known spell. Check 'all spells'.

Help on spell: Chain.
Casting time: 7 rounds.
Spell cost: 45 SPs.
Spell type: neutral.
Spell words: Zechan mool gnaur
Affecting stat(s): level and intelligence and spell knowledge.
While it is possible to command an undead minion to move into a desired
direction with the 'control' spell, it would require unnecessary effort
and strain to command the creature every time. Therefore, it is possible
to forge a more permanent link that simply forces the undead to follow the
caster around blindly. The negative energies surging inside the undead will
cause this spell to fade after a certain amount of time that depends on the
caster's level, intelligence and spell knowledge.

Help on spell: chain lightning
There is no help available for this spell. (UNKNOWN)
No such known spell. Check 'all spells'.

Help on spell: Channel life.
Casting time: 2 rounds.
Spell cost: 20 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: magical.
Spell words: solis daenaelus.
This spell gives a cleric a potent weapon against the undead.  The
cleric can literally give of her own life force, destroying the
negative energies that animate the being.  Upon successful use of this.
Spell, the cleric takes a good deal of damage, while the undead
receiving the life energy is literally torn apart.  The cleric's
skill in various healing spells affects the outcome of this.
Spell to a great degree.  Anti-undead spells such as banish undead
also allow the caster knowledge of an undead's weaknesses, thereby
increasing the damage dealt.

Help on spell: Chant of death.
Casting time: 5 rounds.
Spell cost: 375 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: physical.
Spell words: Death death death...aragaraum death esheer.
With this spell the death knight can demolish the will to live of
any good monster. The effectiveness of the spell depends on casters int,
wis, spell %, skill % of mastery of death illusions and the total amount
of death points the knight possesses. If the spell is succesful the target
will get very depressed about the state of its life and become much more
willing to die, hence easier to hit with spells and skills. This spell
can't be stacked and the knight has to recover from the previous cast
before he can cast it again. The recovery time depends on the power of
the previous chant of death the knight casted.

Help on spell: Chant of fortitude.
Casting time: 1 round.
Spell cost: 600 SPs.
Spell type: enchantment.
Spell words: You miserable bags of bones!  Sally Forth!.
Of all the spells that a bard may use to infuse her music,
few are as awe-inspiring as this one.  The bard actually
causes her audience to begin emitting a shimmering layer
of pure fortitude from inside, causing many attacks to
fall short of their intended target.

Help on spell: Chant of the beast.
Casting time: 6 rounds.
Spell cost: 550 SPs.
Spell type: enchantment.
Spell words: The devil inside, The devil inside....
By chanting a dark and forboding song, the bard can inspire her
audience to incredible ferocity and berzerk power.  This song
is actually able to inspire members of the audience into striking
extra times every combat round, causing a huge amount of damage
to one's foes.  It is known that the ability to perform this
song is very draining on the bard; the less people the bard
must influence, the more powerful the effect from this song
will be.  Most bards report that they receive the best effect
while in smaller groups of people.

Help on spell: Chaos bolt.
Casting time: 3 rounds.
Spell cost: 91 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: random.
Spell words: SUMANI BUUM
Affecting stat(s): int.
This spell will send an uncontrolled bolt of energy
at the target, causing variable types and amounts of.
Damage.  The sp cost of this spell is
also known to vary randomly.

Help on spell: Chaos cube.
Casting time: 5 rounds.
Spell cost: 199 SPs.
Spell type: neutral.
Spell words: Kaei aradus siirwe.
Using this spell the knight can create a cube of pure chaos energy
which will be impassable from both sides to everyone else but the
knight who can exit it from the inside. This spell has two uses, it
can be used as a refuge place for the knight or it can be used to imprison
creatures inside the cube. The target, if not knight, has a saving throw
according to its intelligence and level. The duration of the cube depends
on wis, spell % and skill % of mastery of death protection. The cube can be
broken at any time by the caster with a command 'break_cube'. Due to
the heavy stress caused by handling large amounts of chaos materia this.
Spell can't be casted all the time. The investigations of chaos materia
suggest that all materia of another type except living or dead tissue
will be destroyed if in contact with the materia when the cube collapses,
hence the cube shouldn't be used as a weapon/armour storage.
Note: certain monsters with special teleportation abilities are known
have escaped the chaos cubes.
Additional note: Very large monsters are almost immune to cubing.

Help on spell: Chaos immolation.
Casting time: 3 rounds.
Spell cost: 240 SPs.
Spell type: neutral.
Spell words: Ultimatum chaosium orbeee.
This spell will create a orb of pure chaos energy around the death
knight which will constantly set aflame small parts of the bodies
of the good aligned monsters near the knight, causing continuous.
Damage. The orb will follow its creator everywhere and drain the
creators spell points in order to maintain itself. The knight can
banish the orb at any time with 'banish_orb'
Note: Due to the chaotic nature of this spell the orb will explode
violently if it becomes in contact with another chaos orb causing
great damage to its surroundings. The damage caused by the orb is
determined by casters intelligence, wisdom and level. It is also
rumoured that members of the high council are favoured by the
gods with extra damage.

Help on spell: chaos lance
There is no help available for this spell. (UNKNOWN)
No such known spell. Check 'all spells'.

Help on spell: Chaos wall.
Casting time: 3 rounds.
Spell cost: 134 SPs.
Spell type: defensive.
Spell words: Illus wallis.
Using this spell the knight can fashion a piece of wall from chaos
materia which looks exactly like the walls near it. Only death knights,
necromancers and monsters over level 70 can see thru the illusion. The
knight can remove the wall at any time with command 'disrupt_wall'. It
can also be destroyed by a certain amount of any damagetype. Those who
don't see the actual nature of the chaos wall only see a dead end where
it stands. The duration of the spell depends on mastery of death illusion,
wisdom and amount of death points the knight possesses.
Note: if the wall comes into contact with any other chaos materia it
will instantly collapse.

Help on spell: Charm pigeon.
Casting time: 2 rounds.
Spell cost: 50 SPs.
Spell type: charm.
Spell words: brawwk brawwk join me!.
This spell allows a bard to dominate the small, weak mind
of a pigeon, allowing it to be used for combat, or for
his pigeon roost.  Only certain pigeons may be charmed,
and pigeon deities are completely immune to this.
Higher percents in this spell greatly increase the general
competence and loyalty of the pigeon you have charmed.

Help on spell: Charm undead.
Casting time: 6 rounds.
Spell cost: 401 SPs.
Spell type: special.
Spell words: Undeadis meerk follo.
This spell is one of the most sophisticated ones of the death magic.
It will allow the knight to charm other undeads to serve and follow
him. Controlling undeads drains magical energy all the time though
so it's not wise to keep many undeads at once. If the knight runs
out of magical energy the undeads will become mindless creatures again
and attack the knight. The spellcost of this spell is highly dependant
on wis and the skill % of focus death magic.

Help on spell: Chill touch.
Casting time: 2 rounds.
Spell cost: 1 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: cold.
Spell words: Dhzethandz.
An advanced priest of evil can summon a pair of ethereal hands that
will proceed to strangle their target. Because of the ethereal nature
of the hands the victim won't be suffocated but the hands are from the
plane of dead and thus will cause the victim's body to freeze.

Help on spell: Chill weapon.
Casting time: 12 rounds.
Spell cost: 145 SPs.
Spell type: neutral.
Spell words: selrow louclarem tinomo
Affecting stat(s): level, spell percentage and and air lore.
This spell creates an aura of magical cold around a weapon.  Some
of the weapon's damage will now be 'cold' damage instead of the
usual 'physical' damage.  Casting this spell on a weapon that does
nonphysical damage already may produce peculiar results.  The
target weapon must be on the ground in the same room as the caster.

Help on spell: Choke.
Casting time: 3 rounds.
Spell cost: 245 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: asphyxiation.
Maximum damage: 705.
Spell words: meht ekohc
Affecting stat(s): level, spell percent and mastery of psychokinetics.
Knowing the ways of advanced psychokinetics the psionicist forces his/her mind
to produce two quasi-real hands that choke the foe.

Help on spell: Chorus of serenity.
Casting time: 6 rounds.
Spell cost: 200 SPs.
Spell type: enchantment.
Spell words: Afterall, you don't want a flea collar, do you?.
A bard can soothe even the most savage of beasts with his
music, and the same is true of were-beasts too.  This powerful
song influences any were-creatures in the bard's potential
audience, actually releasing them from the curse while they
are in presence of the bard.

Help on spell: Circle of darkness.
Casting time: 4 rounds.
Spell cost: 226 SPs.
Spell type: defensive.
Spell words: Dras dark circulos.
This spell will summon a circle of ultimate darkness, the essence of
the darkness itself. Everyone else but the servants of death will be
completely blind inside this circle. This spell is best for clouding
your presence from your enemies. The duration of the circle is dependant
on casters wis, spell % and skill % of mastery of death protection.

Help on spell: Circle of life.
Casting time: 5 rounds.
Spell cost: 185 SPs.
Spell type: special.
Spell words: tehad si tno teh den.
Circle of Life is similar in effect to Holy Hand.  The key
difference is that Circle of Life affects all the undead in
a single room.

Help on spell: Circle of protection.
Casting time: 12 rounds.
Spell cost: 123 SPs.
Spell type: defensive.
Spell words: Circulos aras protecto.
This spell will allow the death knight to protect someone with a circle
which can fend off some of the damage of any damagetype specified by
the knight. The protection value can also be specified by the knight
by a number from one to ten. The circle will drain knights spellpoints
in order to maintain itself every time the target inside the circle
takes damage. The circle will disappear if the target dies, leaves the
realm or if the knight runs out of sp. This spell can not be stacked
with any major nonknight-protections like abjurer prots. It also isn't
as powerful as abjurer prots, death knights are not abjurers.
How many targets the knight can protect simultaneously depends on his
dk-rank. The highest protection amount the knight can use depend on.
Spell %, skill % of mastery of death protection and wisdom.
Syntax: cast circle of protection at <target>,<type>,<amount>.

Help on spell: Clairvoyance.
Casting time: 1 round.
Spell cost: 10 SPs.
Spell type: neutral.
Spell words: ala tule paha kakku tule hyva.
Clairvoyance is quite a commonly used ability amongst blind races,
and others lacking some of the important senses common to the human race.
The spell allows the caster to gain some insights about her surroundings.
The sense will enlighten the caster about the environment and the
presence of living creatures. While it has only a limited range, one
can also concentrate on the surroundings of a nearby room.

Help on spell: Claris' melody of mana.
Casting time: 1 round.
Spell cost: 600 SPs.
Spell type: enchantment.
Spell words: Who is the greatest sorcerer in the land?.
Bards whom are skilled in this powerful song have the ability
to lift their target's mana restoration by a great amount.
The audience also finds it much easier to comprehend and
understand the mysteries of ancient magic.

Help on spell: Cleansing harmony.
Casting time: 3 rounds.
Spell cost: 468 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: magical.
Spell words: Efil fo ied.
This spell summons forth the forces of harmony upon an undying creature
that holds no place in this world. The affected creature will instantly
lose some of it's unnatural resistances to damage, as the dark magics binding
it to the realm of living weaken. Once the initial barriers are breached, the
harmonious energies will burn the foul animation as long as the harmonizer can
uphold the spell.
This spell is affected by all harmony related skills as well as mastery of medicine.

Help on spell: Clinging darkness.
Casting time: 6 rounds.
Spell cost: 454 SPs.
Spell type: attack.
Damage type: magical.
Spell words: alecto kalifan.
The spell summons a demonic darkness of extra planar origins to envelop
a target within its inky black tendrils.  The darkness not only inhibits
the target's sight, but gradually infuses their being lowering several of
their stats a great deal over time.

Help on spell: Cloud kill.
Casting time: 4 rounds.
Spell cost: 83 SPs.
Spell type: area attack.
Damage type: asphyxiation.
Maximum damage: 450.
