The high mages of old have long known the existance of Shards. Likewise,
they are aware of the Shards' tendency to appear where a great power leaves
this plane of existance. According to the bibliographical information
gathered by Cemreet from the last hundred and fifty years, the chance of
discovering a Shard of the Gods is much greater when the magical items of
the deceased have been destroyed before its own death.
The precise reason for this is unknown, but the Council of the Mage Guild
speculates that the deconstruction of powerful magical equipment releases
awesome amounts of magical energy. This energy then attracts more power to
the site of combat.
Flash of Power is relatively crude spell designed to boost this effect. The
combined power of three mages is used to overload the magical equipment
carried by a creature, thereby destroying the items, but greatly increasing
the chance and possibly the power of an appearing Shard.

